rest_of_day_open: I see myself being very busy with work. I have a large assignment that is due at 5pm on Friday. That will keep me very busy and focused. I also have dinner plans on Friday evening to celebrate the assignment being done. I am going with my best friend's to a new restaurant.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because we were both open and outgoing ladies. We are both warm and kind people. critical_negative: There were times when she was not as chatty. I did not feel I was leading the conversation quite a bit, which was fine. I am very comfortable leading conversations and keeping them flowing. That being said, I feel she was engaging and easy to talk to. But, not as proactive as I am.

begin_memory_text: We talked some about dogs and spending our lives with them, her dog had recently passed away and my dog had come on camera, so she talked some about the difficult process that it was with having to put her dog down. It was sad, but good, it seemed like she needed to talk about it a bit with someone else. I could definitely relate to her sadness about it, so I think it helped some.
middle_memory_text: We went more over what we do for work, school, and overall lifestyle questions. We talked some about where we live as well, and differences between Washington and Florida, and the weather difference with them.
end_memory_text: I'd mentioned at one point that I'm engaged, so we talked about the ring and how he proposed, and I told her my general plans for the wedding such as when, what I've decided so far, etc. She told me about her and her husband and how they winded up getting married, and how they had lived seperately for a year after getting married due to his work and them both owning condos.
rest_of_day_open: It's going to go really well I think! I'm off to a mini-vacation at the end of the day, which I've been looking forward to for weeks now. So that will be really fun. Although I've been having health issues lately, I'm hoping to have them cleared up and that my doctor's will figure out what's going on there soon. So overall, I see it going well and positively!
critical_positive: She was very good about asking a question, listening and responding well, and then answering the question herself, so there was never really a lull in it. We had meaningful conversation I think, and we connected when we talked about dogs and all of that. We also seemed to enjoy the conversation and wanted to listen to each others answers, as well as give good answers ourselves.
critical_negative: I think she wasn't as humorous or playful as me, so when I'd try to make a little joke or something here and there she mostly brushed past it. It's not a huge thing at all, and not really a negative trait in general too, I'm just an especially goofy individual.
